paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: Extracted information on a BRCA2 variant associated with endometrial cancer in a patient with a history of breast cancer.

individual_records.phenotype_details: Endometrial cancer, previously diagnosed with breast cancer
individual_records.evidence_sentence: A 55-year-old Korean woman who had a past history of breast cancer in her 50s underwent an operation for endometrial cancer.

functional_data.summary: The variant is a missense mutation identified in the BRCA2 gene.

variants.additional_notes: This is the first case report of sequential cancers in a patient with a BRCA2 mutation among a Korean population.
key_quotes: This is first case of a patient with a BRCA2 variation of unknown significance mutation who developed endometrial cancer after breast cancer diagnosis.

extraction_metadata.notes: The extraction was straightforward as the paper provided clear information on the BRCA2 variant.
